<br>
About having PnP invoked on you... ugh.  I hate people who do that.  I think that happened to Tygard a while back while he was camping the Arena aviak spawn.  He was doing the spawns solo, and some guy waltzed right on in and started taking the spawns.  A GM was finally called in, and instructed them to either share the spawn, or one of them was going to have to move.  PnP can be abused so easily this way.  Hell, if I wanted to, I could barge in on a group in LGuk who's camping the Frenzied Ghoul (he drops the FBSS), and demand that they share the camp with me.  After all, PnP says that you have to share if a dispute is brought up, right?  If I see someone camping something, though, I respect their camp, and wait until they leave if I want the camp.  I wish others felt this way, but they don't.<br>
<br>
I agree with the PnP in regards to no KS'ing, no ninja-looting, etc., but this camp-sharing stuff really irritates me.  In that respect, I don't know what would've happened if your situation would've turned ugly.  Maybe, if you would've denied the guy's request to group, he would've just left you alone.  Or maybe he would've gotten whiney and called in a GM.  This is only my opinion, and I don't speak for the entire OC in saying this, but I can't override a GM.  If they say &quot;You <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> have</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to share!&quot; what can we do?  I just hate people who try to force you to share a camp just because of some rule originally made to keep level 60's from farming Guk all day long.   <p><IMG SRC="http://firebeetle.homeip.net/mustelasig.jpg" BORDER="0" WIDTH="216" HEIGHT="212"><br><b>Gnome Heretic of the 54th Bone Chip</b><br>Lanys T'Vyl<br>Proud Officer of <a href="http://www.thesentinent.com">The Sentinent</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub30.ezboard.com/ubrambler.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brambler</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://eqbrambler.homestead.com/files/3dlgowu2.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sentinent Member</span><br>  Posts: 162<br> <font color=#333333>(3/16/01 5:59:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub30.ezboard.com/fthesentinentfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=251.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://eqbrambler.homestead.com/files/leaf.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Guild guide, of sorts</span><hr size=1> I'm curious as to the pnp stuff as well.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
This one should be obvious, but just in case some may not be aware, we are not a guild who advocates the breaking of the Play Nice Policy (PnP). (The PnP guildlines are located here.) If any person is found to be breaking the rules of the PnP, be forewarned that it may mean your permanent expulsion from The Sentinent.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
A big part of the PnP rules is the bit about how a spawn can't be &quot;owned&quot; by someone and if another player wants to bust in on your camp and demand a shot at whatever it is that youre campin, they are within the official rules and they must be allowed a chance at it.  I for one think this is one of the most foolish rules laid out by Verant and does nothing more then promote a lazy and dishonest style of play (camp stealing via pnp or waiting as someone breaks a difficult camp then running in and demanding they share with you, etc etc).  Based on the fact that this is the policy that is most commonly associated with PnP, it would seem appropriate to maybe edit that part of the guide to specifically forbid intentional training, KSing, ninja looting rather then require strict adherence to PnP.  I certainly dont think any of us supports calling in GMs to enforce PnP for camping purposes and I also doubt any of us wouldnt have a good bit of animosity towards anyone who did it to us.  So in essence, as it stands now, I would be breaking guild rules if I camp a rare spawn and then, once the rare pops, I refuse to give some random schmoe whos just walkin by a shot at killin it since he did nothing to break or hold the camp?  Afterall I would be violating pnp..  anyways, just think it might give the wrong idea with its current wording...<br>
<br>
As for the port stuff, you should never ever feel obligated to do a port for someone outta the blue.  Doesnt matter whether they offer you money or not, you arent a public taxi and you and you can always refuse... Especially if you are camping a spot which could easily be lost if you leave.  In these situations I always reply to requests for ports with something like: &quot;Sorry, busy&quot; or &quot;Sorry, hunting&quot;  I've never had a problem with people not taking no for an answer and hope i never do <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .   The other obvious time in which I'll never leave to do a port (unless its an absolute emergency for a guildie or a friend) is when I'm grouped.  Also, /role is your friend, it can come in handy when you are busy and getting alot of port requests (happens alot in Velious since its so far from the mainland), one days like that I usually find turning it on eliminates all requests. <p><IMG SRC="http://eqbrambler.homestead.com/files/sig1.jpg"> <BR>
