As far as your second situation is concerned, alot of grey area there. It all depends on how that other person plays or the attitude he displays. I, personally, have been in that situation (in MM, camping the vampire teeth). I feel that its really weak to invoke the PNR when someone has been camping an item, but due to the fact that PNR's exist, we have to comply. IMO, I would explain to that person what I was camping, and offer to send him/her a tell when I was finished. If he/she wasnt happy with that, I would go ahead and share the camp (reluctlantly) with that person, and ask that I recieve the item up front before it dropped. And if that person still wasnt happy, Id agree on a roll. I understand that just rolling over for someone is rough, but the PNR rules seem to favor those that dont respect others camps, and Ive never won one of those 'I was here first' arguements with a GM...As far as the guild is concerned, diplomacy and courtsy is key, and as long as those are applied to the situation you cant loose and the guild will stand behind you 100%. Hope I helped, and feel free to discount me or piggy back my post you all <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Xaijin, Shaddahkniggit <BR>
